narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend the course to students from art/music/other backgrounds who are interested in working with sound. There are three projects - sound as such, sound and the body, and sound and space, and the LaBelle text is the main text.

If you want to build crazy sound art projects and discuss sound art of the 20th-21st C, take it (no experience necessary). If you just want an easy music/art elective with no real "set" workload, don't.Also, I have no idea what this class would be like with different professors- take it with Brian Kane and Martin Kersels (not that anyone else at Yale could/would teach it)
